title: Hidden Dungeon
data:
The **Hidden Dungeon** is a [dungeon branch](/wiki/Dungeon_branch "Dungeon branch") that appears in [EvilHack](/wiki/EvilHack "EvilHack"). It is an optional one-level branch containing the unique [beholder](/wiki/Beholder_\(EvilHack\) "Beholder (EvilHack)") [Tal'Gath](/wiki/Tal%27Gath "Tal'Gath"), who must be defeated in order to [genocide](/wiki/Genocide "Genocide") beholders.

The entire branch is [non-diggable](/wiki/Non-diggable "Non-diggable"), [no-teleport](/wiki/No-teleport "No-teleport"), and [dark](/wiki/Dark "Dark").

[ ]

- [1 Generation](#Generation)

## Generation

The Hidden Dungeon is accessible through a [magic portal](/wiki/Magic_portal "Magic portal") that always appears in the [Valley of the Dead](/wiki/Valley_of_the_Dead "Valley of the Dead").

[Tal'Gath](/wiki/Tal%27Gath "Tal'Gath") is generated meditating atop a [crystal chest](/wiki/Crystal_chest "Crystal chest") in the top left corner. The chest has a 3‚ÅÑ20 chance of containing a [magic marker](/wiki/Magic_marker "Magic marker"), and also contains two potions, a scroll, a spellbook, an amulet and two rings, all random. One of the buildings is an abandoned [barracks](/wiki/Barracks "Barracks"), and the other is a [mind flayer nursery](/index.php?title=Mind_flayer_nursery\&action=edit\&redlink=1 "Mind flayer nursery (page does not exist)"). Scattered randomly around the level are four [giant cockroaches](/wiki/Giant_cockroach "Giant cockroach"), four [giant leeches](/wiki/Giant_leech "Giant leech"), a [crocodile](/wiki/Crocodile "Crocodile"), a [giant crocodile](/wiki/Giant_crocodile "Giant crocodile"), a [troll](/wiki/Troll "Troll"), a [basilisk](/wiki/Basilisk "Basilisk"), a [beholder](/wiki/Beholder_\(EvilHack\) "Beholder (EvilHack)"), a [magical eye](/wiki/Magical_eye "Magical eye"), two [revenants](/wiki/Revenant "Revenant"), and a [skeleton](/wiki/Skeleton "Skeleton"). Additionally, there are 11 [player monster](/wiki/Player_monster "Player monster") [corpses](/wiki/Corpse "Corpse"), six random [traps](/wiki/Trap "Trap"), and four [rock traps](/wiki/Rock_trap "Rock trap"), all scattered randomly.

html:
Hidden Dungeon

From NetHackWiki
Jump to navigation Jump to search

The Hidden Dungeon is a dungeon branch that appears in EvilHack. It is an optional one-level branch containing the unique beholder Tal'Gath, who must be defeated in order to genocide beholders.

The entire branch is non-diggable, no-teleport, and dark.

Contents

  • 1 Generation
  • 2 Map
  • 3 Strategy
  • 4 History

Generation

The Hidden Dungeon is accessible through a magic portal that always appears in the Valley of the Dead.

Tal'Gath is generated meditating atop a crystal chest in the top left corner. The chest has a 3⁄20 chance of containing a magic marker, and also contains two potions, a scroll, a spellbook, an amulet and two rings, all random. One of the buildings is an abandoned barracks, and the other is a mind flayer nursery. Scattered randomly around the level are four giant cockroaches, four giant leeches, a crocodile, a giant crocodile, a troll, a basilisk, a beholder, a magical eye, two revenants, and a skeleton. Additionally, there are 11 player monster corpses, six random traps, and four rock traps, all scattered randomly.
